File: President Cyril Ramaphosa JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa is yet to decide whether he will pardon King Buyelekhaya Dalindyebo. Three kings have issued an ultimatum to Ramaphosa, saying he should release Dalindyebo or kiss their subjects votes goodbye. The deadline for Ramaphosa to make a decision was on Monday. READ: King Dalindyebo matter must be handled with care: Ramaphosa The AbaThemubu king was sentenced to 12 years in prison for assault, arson, kidnapping and defeating the ends of justice and has served 4 years of his sentence. He "disciplined" a group of people by torching their homes, administering corporal punishment and kidnapping the family of a man who failed to present himself before his court. The Congress of Traditional Leaders of South Africa says King Dalindyebo acted within his rights.